  "text": "The Okuda classification was first applied in HCC patients more than two decades ago. It indicates parameters about the tumor stage (more or less than 50% of the liver parenchyma involved), as well as liver functional status, such as albumin, ascites and bilirubin. Okuda classification has been useful to identify the end-stage patients (Okuda stage III) [CITATION_1] .",
